01:06:44.000 --> 01:06:55.000
Well, one of the things I present myself to individuals in a manner to let them know that I am one of you.

01:06:55.000 --> 01:07:01.000
I'm not no big IOU or somebody.

01:07:01.000 --> 01:07:11.000
And then the next thing was the strong civil rights movement we had in Holmes County.

01:07:11.000 --> 01:07:30.000
And then the next thing was I got a chance to have contact with those 300 plus adults that were coming to the migrant farmer school.

01:07:30.000 --> 01:07:40.000
For example, if one was coming in, you know, lead a field and head in there and have a flat.

01:07:40.000 --> 01:07:43.000
And he would get there for to be that four o'clock.

01:07:43.000 --> 01:07:51.000
And he'd get that five o'clock. And the teachers given in the devil, I would allow the teachers to do it.

01:07:51.000 --> 01:07:54.000
I would allow the teachers to do it.

01:07:54.000 --> 01:08:00.000
And let's couple of minutes for getting here at all. See, those were poor folks.

01:08:00.000 --> 01:08:17.000
And definitely, and definitely, those 300 plus black folks that I got a chance to be the director of, they was a part of the group that put me over.

01:08:17.000 --> 01:08:25.000
Plus the fact, the strong civil rights movement that we had.

01:08:25.000 --> 01:08:36.000
And mental to pound, when I taught, and let's not tell, mental to pound had heard that children talk about me.

01:08:36.000 --> 01:08:39.000
And they knew the kind of person that I was.

01:08:39.000 --> 01:08:50.000
You certainly had a strong reputation. Tell us about your opponent and the tactics of that campaign.

01:08:50.000 --> 01:08:55.000
Well, I ran as an independent.

01:08:55.000 --> 01:09:03.000
I felt why you didn't run as a, you decided you all decided not to run in the Democratic primary, but to run as independence in the fall.

01:09:03.000 --> 01:09:08.000
We could not, we could not be members of the Democratic Party.

01:09:08.000 --> 01:09:12.000
We could not be members of the Democratic Party.

01:09:12.000 --> 01:09:21.000
However, I decided to run once, because the end of the business never been to the pole before.

01:09:21.000 --> 01:09:27.000
You know, they may get tired of coming out. So just take it one shot.

01:09:27.000 --> 01:09:32.000
So we decided to run as independence.

01:09:32.000 --> 01:09:34.000
All right.

01:09:34.000 --> 01:09:38.000
J.P. Love and Wilbur Huckel.

01:09:38.000 --> 01:09:42.000
They had two representatives from the home kind of before.

01:09:42.000 --> 01:09:47.000
But the federal government had intervened and they had to redistrict.

01:09:47.000 --> 01:09:50.000
And they had one district.

01:09:50.000 --> 01:09:55.000
So J.P. Love and Ed Wilbur Huckel ran against each other.

01:09:55.000 --> 01:09:58.000
And the primary.

01:09:58.000 --> 01:10:02.000
And J.P. Love warned.

01:10:02.000 --> 01:10:08.000
And that's who I met in the general election.

01:10:08.000 --> 01:10:13.000
And he's the one that amazed you a few minutes ago that contested the election.

01:10:13.000 --> 01:10:16.000
He contested the whole away in front of speaking.

01:10:16.000 --> 01:10:23.000
I didn't know until 15 minutes before I was seated that I was going to be seated.

01:10:23.000 --> 01:10:28.000
Million right was my lead lawyer.

01:10:28.000 --> 01:10:32.000
But he contested all the way.

01:10:32.000 --> 01:10:38.000
Were there any tactics of intimidation during that campaign?

01:10:38.000 --> 01:10:41.000
Were Blacks free to vote at the poles?

01:10:41.000 --> 01:10:46.000
Or were there being questions? We see a lot of that going on now.

01:10:46.000 --> 01:10:50.000
You certainly got to vote out. You got to vote out.

01:10:50.000 --> 01:11:01.000
In 1967, the Blacks didn't allow other Blacks to be afraid or be intimidated.

01:11:01.000 --> 01:11:03.000
Because they were there.

01:11:03.000 --> 01:11:08.000
And we had not official poll watches.

01:11:08.000 --> 01:11:11.000
But we had watches of God's.

01:11:11.000 --> 01:11:16.000
We would call them at every present at every voting place.

01:11:16.000 --> 01:11:22.000
And they knew that they was going to be protected if they came to the polls.

01:11:22.000 --> 01:11:25.000
And that didn't happen in some other counties.

01:11:25.000 --> 01:11:28.000
Pardon? That did not happen in some other counties.

01:11:28.000 --> 01:11:29.000
Oh yes.

01:11:29.000 --> 01:11:30.000
We're a diminutive.

01:11:30.000 --> 01:11:32.000
Yes, yes, I know.

01:11:32.000 --> 01:11:33.000
Yes, from voting.

01:11:33.000 --> 01:11:35.000
So you won the election.

01:11:35.000 --> 01:11:39.000
And it must have been quite a party that night.

01:11:39.000 --> 01:11:44.000
Yes, I won the election.

01:11:44.000 --> 01:11:53.000
The first night that we had, I mean, the first time I ran in.

01:11:53.000 --> 01:11:58.000
I was running behind.

01:11:58.000 --> 01:12:00.000
All right.

01:12:00.000 --> 01:12:05.000
