01:13:13.000 --> 01:13:16.000
What do you remember about that?

01:13:16.000 --> 01:13:29.000
Well, we went through quite a few lawsuits and Marion Wright was my lead lawyer.

01:13:29.000 --> 01:13:35.000
And the first day, I didn't know if I would be seated or not.

01:13:35.000 --> 01:13:40.000
Until 15 minutes before I was seated.

01:13:40.000 --> 01:13:51.000
When Marion Wright came back on the outside, where I was on the south side of the Capitol, and told me Robert, they have decided to seat you.

01:13:51.000 --> 01:14:04.000
And then when I went in, again, because of my experience at Michigan State and Western Michigan University,

01:14:04.000 --> 01:14:12.000
the being one black among 121 white, that did not intimidate me at all.

01:14:12.000 --> 01:14:15.000
Because I knew what I knew.

01:14:15.000 --> 01:14:26.000
And one thing that I knew, what I was going to zero in on, was what I was an expert in, and that was education.

01:14:26.000 --> 01:14:34.000
And I knew no one there knew as much about education as I did.

01:14:34.000 --> 01:14:37.000
But you had to wait a while.

01:14:37.000 --> 01:14:41.000
I think for about eight years, you were the only black in the legislature.

01:14:41.000 --> 01:14:55.000
Yes, I was on the black and the legislation when I went in about first day, the regulations of the House walls, you know, you had districts.

01:14:55.000 --> 01:15:06.000
And the senior person in that district would choose the seating far, the rest of the members, and here's a her district.

01:15:06.000 --> 01:15:17.000
So on this side, where I'm sitting now, that's the door where you come in, right in front of me. That's the door.

01:15:17.000 --> 01:15:25.000
All right. And this first line was two seats. All right.

01:15:25.000 --> 01:15:30.000
And then I'll come between us, and that's three seats.

01:15:30.000 --> 01:15:41.000
So the old gentleman that was the senior of my delegation, he chose this seat for me. This seat for me.

01:15:41.000 --> 01:15:51.000
And his seat is crossed our from me. Then the other member from my other district, his seat across the aisle from me.

01:15:51.000 --> 01:16:01.000
All right. Now, the vacant seat is far the speaker of the house. When able to speak of the house is not preside.

01:16:01.000 --> 01:16:09.000
